  "text": "Women in low-income settings often consume inadequate amount of micronutrients because of resource limitation. They have a limited intake of animal source foods, fruits and vegetables. Intake of micronutrients less than the recommended values increase women's risk of micronutrient deficiencies [CITATION_1] . Adequate nutritional status of women is important for good health and increased work capacity of women themselves as well as for the health of their offspring [CITATION_2] .",
